commitResults.messageTitle: Implemented Rename, Greet, Exit for Nig Chatbot
Store text entered by user, display when requested
Add the ability to mark tasks as done or undone
commitResults.messageBody:
Created a Task class to track "isDone" for each object
Nig chatbot now looks out for "mark" or "unmark" and will set isDone
to true or false for the respective task number

commitResults.messageTitle: Tweak code to comply with coding standards

commitResults.messageBody:
Todo, Deadline, Event inherit from superclass Task
Override toString

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Support for Tracking Three Types of Tasks
commitResults.messageBody:
ToDos: tasks without any date/time attached to it e.g., visit new theme park
Deadlines: tasks that need to be done before a specific date/time e.g., submit report by 11/10/2019 5pm
Events: tasks that start at a specific date/time and ends at a specific date/time

Code Quality: Refactored code to apply SLAP principles

Added error handling for the following scenarios:
UnknownCommandException - not a valid command
EmptyBodyException - valid command, but empty after
BadFormatException - valid command, incorrect usage
